The paper discusses recent developments in unsupervised representation learning in NLP, which is a subfield of computer science focused on natural language processing. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of larger corpora and advances in parallel computing, which are relevant to machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE). Finally, the paper mentions the use of language models in computer vision tasks, which could potentially place it in the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category.
